<item>
            <title>[LU-11719] Refactor search_itree</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11719</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The behavior of search_itree is different from its close relative search_queue in ways that are a little confusing.&#160; Also, in some cases, it will continue searching the trees after a lock has been found.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is a low priority bug to slightly refactor its behavior, inspired because the difference between search_itree and search_queue introduced a subtle bug in the &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11670&quot; title=&quot;Incorrect size when using lockahead&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-11670&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-11670&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; patch.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
